        "name": "Reliance on Insufficiently Trustworthy Component"
      },
      "notes": [
        {
          "category": "summary",
          "text": "Hitachi Energy is aware of publicly disclosed reports of multiple vulnerabilities in open-source software components (OpenSSL and Node.JS) used in the Gateway Station (GWS) product. Versions are available to remediate the identified vulnerabilities.CVE-2020-1968, CVE-2020-8172, CVE-2020-8174, CVE-2020-8201, CVE-2020-8252, CVE-2020-8265, and CVE-2020-8287 have been assigned to these vulnerabilities in open source components used by GWS. A CVSS v3 base score of 8.1 has been calculated for the worst case; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H).\n",
          "title": "Vulnerability Summary"
        }
      ],
